HEADWORD: Professoriate
<hw>Pro`fes*so"ri*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The body of professors, or the professorial staff, in a university
or college.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A professorship.</def>⟦br⟧
